    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                        <date>March 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></date>
                        <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>Though you are so considerate as to tell me not to write (&amp; in truth my correspondence is very heavy) I must thank you for your very curious case of the peculiar form of quasi inheritance, where many descendants from the same parents are similarly affected.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> This holds good in a remarkable manner with the deaf- &amp; dumb; &amp; is, I believe, quite inexplicable.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
                        <p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
               
                
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">interl before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="print">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>
                
                
                
            </div>
           
           
           <div type="footnotes">
               <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7593.xml">letter from Lewin Hill, 17 March 1871</ref> (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19).</note>
               <note xml:id="foot.f2">Lewin Hill had written to CD that ten out of the thirty members of his generation of his father’s family had a defective right knee joint (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 19, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7593.xml">letter from Lewin Hill, 17 March 1871</ref>).</note>
               <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 2: 22.</note>
            </div>
        
